		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">The ultimate goal of the proposed research is to strengthen the background knowledge on the role of anions on structural and physical properties of inorganic solids. This objective will be pursued via preparation and characterisation of mated-anion compounds, i.e. compounds containing more than one type of anions. Mixed-anion compounds will be prepared, as single crystal, via reactions of molten reactants on metal surfaces and, as polycrystalline materials, via reactions in molten zinc. The applicant intends to explore fully the potential of these two original techniques as general routes for the preparation of non-oxide materials. The structural and physical properties of the products will be characterised and compared as functions of the size, charge and electronegativity of the anions. The results of this work will benefit the solid-state community in its whole, by contributing to the construction of a basic genera! knowledge on the behaviour of anions in inorganic solids. Ultimately, this will lead to the preparation of materials of an unusual and potentially useful kind.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
